{{pp-pc1}} {{further|Cause of death}}{{Update|date=September 2017}} The following is a '''list of the causes of human deaths''' worldwide for the year 2002, arranged by their associated [[mortality rate]]s. There were 57,029,000 deaths tabulated for that year. Some causes listed include deaths also included in more specific subordinate causes (as indicated by the "Group" column), and some causes are omitted, so the percentages do not sum to 100. According to the [[World Health Organization]], about 58 million people died in 2005, using the [[International Statistical Classification of Diseases and Related Health Problems]] (ICD).<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.who.int/cancer/en/ | year = 2005 | author = WHO | title = Cancer }}</ref> According to the Institute for Health Metrics and Evaluation, 52.77 million people died in 2010.<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Lozano|first1=Rafael|last2=Naghavi|first2=Mohsen|title=Global and regional mortality from 235 causes of death for 20 age groups in 1990 and 2010: a systematic analysis for the Global Burden of Disease Study 2010|journal=Lancet|date=Dec 2012|doi=10.1016/S0140-6736(12)61728-0|url=http://ipa-world.org/society-resources/code/images/95b1494-Lozano%20Mortality%20GBD2010.pdf|display-authors=1|pmid=23245604|volume=380|issue=9859|pages=2095–128}}</ref>
