== Malnutrition ==
Malnutrition can be identified as an underlying cause for shortened life.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tropej.oxfordjournals.org/content/2/2/77.extract |title=Mortality In Second And Third Degree Malnutrition |publisher=Tropej.oxfordjournals.org |date=2014-06-03 |accessdate=2014-06-09}}</ref> 70% of childhood deaths (age 0-4) are reportedly due to diarrheal illness, acute respiratory infection, malaria and immunizable disease. However, of these childhood deaths, 56% can be attributed to the effects of malnutrition as an underlying cause.<ref>{{Cite journal|pmc=2486780 |title=The effects of malnutrition on child mortality in developing countries |date=2014-01-24 |pmid=7554015 |volume=73 |issue=4 |journal=Bull. World Health Organ. |pages=443–8 |vauthors=Pelletier DL, Frongillo EA, Schroeder DG, Habicht JP }}</ref> The effects of malnutrition include increased susceptibility to infection,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ajcn.nutrition.org/content/27/6/638.short |title=Some effects of malnutrition on the immune response in man |publisher=Ajcn.nutrition.org |date=1974-06-01 |accessdate=2014-06-09}}</ref> musculature wasting, skeletal deformities and neurologic development delays.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pediatric.theclinics.com/article/S0031-3955(09)00086-8/abstract |title=Elsevier |publisher=Pediatric.theclinics.com |date= |accessdate=2014-06-09}}</ref> According to the World Health Organization, malnutrition is named as the biggest contributor to child mortality<ref>{{cite web|author1=Stay informed today |author2=every day |url=http://www.economist.com/node/10566634 |title=Malnutrition: The starvelings |publisher=The Economist |date=2008-01-24 |accessdate=2014-06-09}}</ref> with 36 million deaths in 2005 related to malnutrition.<ref>Ziegler, Jean (2007). [[L'Empire de la honte]]. Fayard</ref>
==Developed vs. developing economies== Top causes of death, according to the [[World Health Organization]] report for the calendar year 2001:<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ucatlas.ucsc.edu/cause.php |title=Cause of Death |last= |first= |date=18 February 2004 |website=UC Atlas of Global Inequality |publisher=University of California, Santa Cruz |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140618212442/http://ucatlas.ucsc.edu/cause.php |archive-date=18 June 2014 |accessdate=2014-06-09 |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref>
