{{orphan|date=August 2015}}
'''Museum Night''' ({{lang-nl|Museumnacht}}) is an annual event in several cities in [[Flanders]] and [[Netherlands|the Netherlands]]. [[Museum]]s will collaborate and people will be able to buy one ticket to access all the participating museums in a particular city.

One of the most popular events is Museum Night in Amsterdam <ref>http://museumnachtamsterdam.nl/</ref> {{nl icon}}, but other events are also held in cities like [[Almere]], [[Antwerp]], [[Breda]], [[Brussels]], [[The Hague]], [[Delft]],<ref>http://www.museumnachtdelft.nl/</ref> [[Ghent]], [[Leiden]], [[Ostend]], [[Roermond]], [[Rotterdam]], [[Utrecht]] and many more.<ref>{{cite web|title=Museumnacht|url=http://museumnachtamsterdam.nl/|website=museumnachtamsterdam.nl|publisher=N8|accessdate=2 November 2014|language=Dutch}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Museumnacht|url=http://www.iamsterdam.com/nl-NL/Ndtrc/Museumnacht|website=http://www.iamsterdam.com/|publisher=Municipality of Amsterdam|accessdate=2 November 2014|location=Amsterdam|language=Dutch}}</ref>

The participating Amsterdam museums are yearly opened on the first Saturday of November from 7 pm until 2 am the next day. Besides the normal exhibitions in museums, activities are arranged, like artist performances and free guides. In some events, public transport can be freely used for people who bought a ticket.<ref>{{cite web|title=Museumnacht|url=http://museumnachtamsterdam.nl/info|website=museumnachtamsterdam.nl|publisher=N8|accessdate=2 November 2014|language=Dutch}}</ref>

