{{Infobox recurring event|name=Penang Hot Air Balloon Fiesta|native_name=|image=[[File:Penang Hot Air Balloon.jpg|300px]]|imagesize=frameless|caption=|date=February|begins=|frequency=Annually|location=[[File:Seal_of_George_Town.svg|20x20px]] [[George Town, Penang|George Town]], [[Penang]]|first=2015|last=|attendance=170,000 (2017)<ref name=BM>{{Cite news|url=http://www.buletinmutiara.com/download/2017/BuletinMutiaraFeb22017-BM.pdf|title=Penang Hot Air Balloon Fiesta 2017 memberangsangkan, jumpa lagi tahun depan!|last=Wardah Sohilli|first=Ainul|date=16 February 2017|work=Buletin Mutiara|access-date=}}</ref>|genre=[[Hot air balloon festival]]|budget=|website={{URL|penanghotairballoonfiesta.com/}}|footnotes=|country={{flag|Malaysia}}|venue=Polo Ground|organised=AKA Balloon Sdn Bhd<ref name=BM />|next=24 - 25 February 2018<ref name=Star>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thestar.com.my/metro/metro-news/2017/12/23/glowing-balloon-attractions-displays-a-prelude-to-penang-hot-air-balloon-fiesta-2018/|title=Displays a prelude to Penang Hot Air Balloon Fiesta 2018 - Metro News {{!}} The Star Online|website=www.thestar.com.my|access-date=2017-12-24}}</ref>}}
{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2017}}{{Use British English|date=December 2017}}
The '''Penang Hot Air Balloon Fiesta''' is an annual [[hot air balloon festival]] held within the city of [[George Town, Penang|George Town]] in [[Penang]], [[Malaysia]]. The festival, organised by AKA Balloon Sdn Bhd, a Malaysian private limited firm, takes place every February at the city's Polo Ground.<ref name="BM" /><ref name="Star" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mypenang.gov.my/events/all-events/103/|title=myPenang|website=mypenang.gov.my|access-date=2017-12-24}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://penanghotairballoonfiesta.com/|title=Penang Hot Air Balloon Fiesta 2016|last=Tourism|first=Penang Global|work=Penang Hot Air Balloon Fiesta 2016|access-date=2017-12-24}}</ref>
Inaugurated in 2015, the two-day Penang Hot Air Balloon Fiesta typically features 15 hot air balloons, with the participating crew coming from various nations such as [[Malaysia]], the [[Netherlands]], [[Belgium]] and the [[United States]].<ref name="BM" /><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.lonelyplanet.com/malaysia/george-town/events/penang-hot-air-balloon-fiesta/a/poi-fes/1548146/357010|title=Penang Hot Air Balloon Fiesta in George Town, Malaysia|last=Planet|first=Lonely|work=Lonely Planet|access-date=2017-12-24|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.thesundaily.my/news/2098537|title=More visitors expected for Penang Hot Air Balloon Fiesta next year|website=www.thesundaily.my|language=en|access-date=2017-12-24}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.onlypenang.com/penang-attractions/penang-hot-air-balloon-fiesta-2016/|title=Penang Hot Air Balloon Fiesta 2016 - OnlyPenang.com|last=OnlyPenang|date=2016-01-24|work=OnlyPenang|access-date=2017-12-24|language=en-US}}</ref> The previous edition of the festival in 2017 attracted as many as 170,000 visitors.<ref name="Star" />
== History == The Penang Hot Air Balloon Fiesta, the first [[hot air balloon festival]] in the [[Penang|State of Penang]], was mooted to boost tourist arrivals into the city-state.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.theedgemarkets.com/article/edgy-gig-sky|title=#edGY: A gig in the sky|date=2015-02-27|work=The Edge Markets|access-date=2017-12-24}}</ref><ref name=":0">{{Cite news|url=http://www.themalaymailonline.com/malaysia/article/penang-to-host-first-hot-air-balloon-fiesta-next-month#BxCe60UCGO58i3qj.97|title=Penang to host first hot air balloon fiesta next month|date=2015-01-26|access-date=2017-12-24}}</ref> The inaugural event, held at the Polo Ground on 21 and 22 February 2015, was timed to coincide with the [[Chinese New Year]] festivities.<ref name=":0" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.thesundaily.my/news/1335561|title=Penang Hot Air Balloon Fiesta a hit among locals and tourists|website=www.thesundaily.my|language=en|access-date=2017-12-24}}</ref>
Since then, the event has grown considerably. Several on-site family-friendly activities have been added into the two-day event, including workshops, photography contests and [[Kite|kite flying]].<ref name=":1">{{Cite web|url=https://www.penang.gov.my/en/dmedia/3512-penang-hot-air-balloon-mini-fiesta|title=Portal Rasmi Kerajaan Negeri Pulau Pinang - Penang Hot Air Balloon Mini Fiesta|last=Zabidi|first=Nor Diana|website=www.penang.gov.my|language=en-gb|access-date=2017-12-24}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.timeout.com/penang/things-to-do/penang-hot-air-balloon-fiesta|title=Penang Hot Air Balloon Fiesta|work=Time Out Penang|access-date=2017-12-24|language=en}}</ref> Smaller-scale preludes to the yearly event have been organised as well, such as a mini balloon fiesta at the [[Esplanade, Penang|Esplanade]] and a balloon display in [[Butterworth, Penang|Butterworth]] on the [[Seberang Perai|mainland]].<ref name="BM" /><ref name=":1" />
